--- Basic 2D: two well-separated clusters ---
(0,0)	3
(100,100)	2
--- Same-cell merge (cell side d/sqrt(2) ~= 0.707 for d=1) ---
(0.3,0.3)	3
--- Cross-cell merge: horizontal, vertical, diagonal ---
(0,0)	2
(10,11)	2
(20,20)	2
--- Chain through 3 cells ---
(0,0)	3
--- No merge: points just over distance d ---
(0,0)	1
(3,0)	1
--- d = 0: behaves like plain GROUP BY (x, y) ---
(1,1)	2
(2,2)	1
--- Negative coordinates ---
(-5,-5)	2
(5,5)	1
--- Integer cluster key ---
(2,2)	2
(100,100)	1
--- With non-cluster key ---
a	(0,0)	2
b	(0,0)	1
b	(100,100)	1
--- Single row ---
(42,42)	1
--- Multiple aggregate functions ---
(0,0)	3	6	1	3
(100,100)	1	10	10	10
--- Large d collapses everything ---
1
--- EXPLAIN PIPELINE shows ClusterMergingTransform ---
1
--- EXPLAIN PLAN shows Cluster dimensions: 2 ---
1
